Metadata: New diterpenoids from the Caribbean gorgonian "Eunicea calyculata". Photochemical interconversion of the cembrene and cubitene skeletons

Early chemical investigations of "Eunicea" species, beginning in the early 1960s, showed these animals to be a chemically complex resource for cembrene lactones. More recent studies have shown that this gorgonian genus produces a wider diversity of secondary metabolites. Seven new diterpenoids of the cubitane and cembrane classes have been isolated from the Caribbean sea whip "Eunicea calyculata". The first photochemical transformation of a cembrene to a cubitene diterpenoid is reported.
